    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in Mexico (
                        Thurston
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d707</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">707</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-10-16T20:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-10-16T20:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-16T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="707" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d707">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.504 Mexico/10–1647: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-16T19:00:00-06:00">October 16, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1124. Embassy today received Foreign Office note 34231 October 15<note n="56" xml:id="d707fn1">Not printed.</note> referring supplementary agreement for
                    contracting workers in Texas signed January 31 confirmed in exchange of notes of
                    March 10, 1947 (<gloss target="#t_Embdesp1">Embsdes</gloss> 3090 March 14<note n="56" xml:id="d707fn2">Not printed.</note>) and stating that in view fact
                    that as regards Mexican workers in Texas stimulation [<hi rend="italic">stipulations?</hi>] of general agreement have not been fulfilled at least
                    to desired extent and taking account hopes not realized favorably for solving
                    discrimination against Mexicans in Texas. Mexican Government resolved terminate
                    supplementary agreement and consequently will no longer authorize contracts
                    Mexican laborers found illegally in Texas. Copy and translation note being
                    forwarded by pouch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
